Kaizer Chiefs came back from a goal down to beat Mamelodi Sundowns 2-1 at the FNB Stadium in Johannesburg. Sundowns drew first blood through Khama Billiat. Bernard Parker got the equaliser before half-time. And late in the game Sundowns defender Bangaly Soumahoro handed Chiefs the win with a bizarre own-goal. Meanwhile, Free State Stars convincingly beat struggling Orlando Pirates 3-2 at James Motlatsi Stadium. The hosts scored four of the goals in the five goal first half thriller. Goalkeeper Thela Ngobeni scored an own goal when he guided the ball into his own net.